title: Scrapbook (USA), 1898–1936
medium: silk samples with watercolor and pencil designs
description: Sample book has 11 samples in fancy cloth weaves, 200 tie silk samples, clippings from newspapers, a note written by Mr. Appel, 55 pencil drawings, 61 designs in pencil and opaque colors, 45 designs in pencil with watercolor.

tombstone.epitaph: Scrapbook (USA), 1898–1936; Manufactured by Appel Brothers Manufacturing Company (United States); silk samples with watercolor and pencil designs; H x W: 31.2 × 11.1 cm (12 5/16 × 4 3/8 in.); 1945-19-1
